      h2 Colors
      p Jersey Blue and Buff are New Jersey’s state colors, assigned with specific color values.
      p The colors were chosen by George Washington while encamped at Jockey Hollow during the Revolutionary War, originally for the New Jersey Line uniform coats.
      p The New Jersey Secretary of State’s Office provides Pantone color values for the colors within the seal.
